  "name": "Hall Sensor LED Trigger",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Hall Sensor LED Trigger",
    "description": "Same Hall power column as lesson 49 (Hall at 270°: + north, − south). At the SIG T-junction, a 10kΩ pull-up feeds USB while SIG also drives 470Ω → red LED → ground. With no magnet the pull-up holds SIG high and the LED stays off; when the Hall output pulls SIG low, current flows through the LED and it snaps on — a clear trigger. Compare lesson 49 (detection) and lesson 51 (switch circuit). LED at 90°."
  },
